  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Shelter for internally displaced populations in Afrin and East Ghouta displacement sites.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project provides life-saving Shelter support to  people displaced from Eastern Ghouta and Afrin. The targeted beneficiary populations are living in collective shelters with little or no existing safe shelter infrastructure in place. As soon as funding for this project is received, DRC will be ready to provide emergency infrastructure support to collective shelters through creation of safe, private living spaces for families in accordance with Shelter sector minimum standards,  provision of partitions in large halls (where people are placed following arrival to collective shelters, before private rooms can be built and allocated to new arrivals), installation of ventilation units in large halls to reduce high temperatures and improve air quality in these halls, and installation of garbage bins to promote safe garbage management and disposal. The project accords with the Shelter sector&#x2019;s strategy to provide emergency shelter interventions to enable people displaced from Eastern Ghouta/Afrin to large collective shelters to live safely, and will together with the interventions of other actors create a safe environment for other humanitarian activities in the sectors of education and child protection to be delivered.</narrative>
  </description>
